    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a clear focus on exploiting favorable matchups against shaky rotation arms. **Gunnar Henderson** (68.83) and **Josh Lowe** (68.79) anchor our offensive production; **Gunnar Henderson** benefits significantly from a dynamic platoon advantage (R) and a lead-off spot against Schlittler, while **Josh Lowe** remains a priority start given the weak 4.38 xERA of Davis Martin and the wind-aided boost in his favor. Meanwhile, **Heliot Ramos** (67.76) serves as a high-upside play; despite the potential for a \"Lineup Pending\" volatility, his combination of a favorable matchup against Randy V\u00e1squez (4.91 xERA) and the current wind conditions makes him an essential component of our daily strategy to chase R and RBI.\n\nWe are carefully monitoring the lineup configurations for **Sam Antonacci** (58.18) and **Miguel Vargas** (50.30), both of whom received a meaningful boost from wind-out projections and confirmed spots in the order against J. Soriano. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (63.07) provides our safest floor, we are taking a cautious approach with **Drake Baldwin** (43.40) and **Liam Hicks** (45.14); both face elite arms in L. Gilbert and A. Nola, respectively, keeping their scores in the marginal tier despite their talent. **Dominic Smith** was the most difficult exclusion from the starting nine, falling just short at 36.59 due to a lower projected spot in the order and the difficulty of facing L. Gilbert. While **Jordan Westburg** and **Luis Robert Jr.** remain sidelined on the IL, we continue to look for ways to integrate our high-speed depth to address our scarcity in SB, keeping an eye on whether **Andy Pages** (49.44) can capitalize on the slow delivery of Okert to steal a base.",
